We’ve created tools to help you manage your data. Please refer to the Privacy Help Center for more information on
how to use these tools
to manage and access your data.
You can download your data from the Google products you use, like your email, calendar, and photos.
In a few easy steps,
create a copy to keep for your records or use the data in another service. Before submitting this form, see
how to download or transfer your data
.
If you don't find what you need,
fill out the
Data Access Request Form
. This form helps us verify your identity, and make sure we only share personal information directly with you.
We’ve created tools to help you manage and delete your data. Please refer to the Privacy Help Center for more information on how to use these tools
to delete your data.
Learn more about
how Google handles security vulnerabilities
.
If you believe you have discovered a vulnerability in a Google product or have a security incident to report, go to
goo.gl/vuln
.
For suspected Google account hacking, please see how to
secure a hacked or compromised account
.
Before submitting this form, learn more about
how to unsubscribe from mass emails
on Gmail.
Promotional and mass emails usually have unsubscribe links at the bottom of the emails.
Keeping users’ information safe and secure is among our highest priorities at Google, and we're committed to complying with applicable data protection laws.
We maintain servers
around the world
to make sure our services are reliable and your information may be processed on servers outside of the country where you live. Regardless of where your information is processed, Google applies the same level of protection to your data. We also comply with certain
legal frameworks
relating to the international transfer of personal data.
