AdPerformance SDK
We provide a custom SDK (Software development Kit) to our customers or their clients which help us to collect information about you on websites or application you visit, so we can measure performance of their TV advertising campaigns.
Our SDK rely on two cookies
Cookie name
Provider
Expiration
Type
Purpose
ry_ry-*_realytics
Realytics
1 year
First party
Store anonymous user id
ry_*_so_realytics
Realytics
30 minutes
First party
Store session id
These cookies allow Realytics to distinguish you among others websites visitors and will be use for audience statistics only. These cookie will support events (aka Tags) transmitted to Realytics to understand customer website user behavior.
By default “events” collect these non-exhaustive additional data in an encrypted way:
Property name
Truncated IP address
Browser information
Operating system
Device identifier
Current URL
Timestamp of the visit
Each customer can collect additional data.
By default all data collected is based on a legitimate purpose and will not be used for other purpose than audience statistics. Consequently these cookies may be exempted of your consent.
Realytics successfully participated in the audience measurement evaluation program conducted by the French Data Protection Authority (the “Cnil”) and can offer the exemption mode in accordance with the Cnil guidelines. Please note that this exemption only applies to France.
Advanced scenarios can be enabled by the customer that may add depth to the measurement provided by the AdPerformance product, like TVRetargeting, Deterministic measurement …
These feature will need your consent to be used and may additionally add these information to the data collected.
Therefore, Realytics never has access to any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person, characterizing a personal data as for article 4-1.
