Public Attestation of Compliance to the Transparency & Consent Framework (TCF)
To our valued partners, clients, and the digital advertising ecosystem,
Realytics SAS, as a proud participant in the digital advertising industry, is committed to upholding the highest standards of data privacy and user consent in alignment with global regulations and industry frameworks. As part of our dedication to transparency and responsible data handling, we hereby publicly attest our compliance with the Transparency and Consent Framework (TCF) established by IAB Europe.
As a registered TCF vendor, we are fully committed to:
Adhering to the TCF Policies
: We ensure that our practices align with the TCF’s guidelines and specifications, designed to facilitate the digital advertising industry’s compliance with the EU’s General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and ePrivacy Directive.
Upholding Transparency and Consent Requirements
: We acknowledge the importance of obtaining explicit and informed consent from users for the processing of personal data and accessing or storing information on a user’s device. Our processes are designed to provide clear, comprehensible, and easily accessible information to users about how their data is used, ensuring their rights are respected and protected.
Implementing TCF Technical Specifications
: Realytics SAS employs the TCF’s technical standards within our operations to support the communication of users’ consent choices across the digital advertising supply chain effectively.
Engagement in Continuous Improvement: We are dedicated to continuously improving our practices in line with evolving regulations, industry standards, and the TCF framework to better serve the interests of users, clients, and partners.
Collaboration with Partners and Regulators
: We actively engage with industry partners, regulatory bodies, and other stakeholders to foster an environment of compliance, trust, and respect for user privacy within the digital ecosystem.
Realytics SAS takes its role in the digital advertising community seriously and is committed to leading by example in compliance, transparency, and user protection.
This public attestation of compliance to the TCF is a testament to our ongoing commitment to these principles.
We welcome inquiries and discussions regarding our compliance practices and are dedicated to working collaboratively with all stakeholders to advance privacy standards in the digital advertising industry
Realytics commited to assess the balance of interest for each TCF purpose that relies on the legitimate interest. The assesments can be read at :
Balance of Interest Assessment according to Art. 6(1)(1) lit. f) GDPR – TV Tracking – Realytics
